Lenovo System Firmware Version 1.59

Important updates

  • It is highly recommended to update Intel Management Engine Firmware to 15.0.42.2235 (n32rg27w) or later.

Lenovo System Firmware Version 1.56

Important updates

  • Update includes a security fix.

New functions or enhancements

  • Updated the Diagnostics module to version 04.26.000.

Problem fixes

  • Fixed an issue where ethernet connection of the Lenovo USB-C to Ethernet Adapter might be disconnected sometimes.
  • Fixed an issue where plugging and unplugging the docking station can cause a Yellow Bang for USB 2.0 devices and can also cause a system hang at reboot.

a083ebc5138e5e071ef7270cc9a8280722cc7adf.Description:
Lenovo System Firmware Version 1.55

Important updates

  • Update includes a security fix.
  • Enhancement to address security vulnerability.

New functions or enhancements

  • Updated the CPU microcode.
  • Updated the Diagnostics module to version 04.25.000.
  • Updated Regulatory Information.
  • Supported Certificate Based BIOS Authentication function.
  • Supported new memory revision.
  • Supported a new option to enable/disable Fingerprint Single-Touch Authentication in BIOS Setup.
  • Supported the firmware update of some devices.

Problem fixes

  • Fixed an issue where SMBIOS Type-2 Chassis Handle does not match to Type-3 Handle.
  • Fixed an issue where there is no display on the external monitor via docking station while Intel Management Engine Firmware is being updated.
  • Fixed an issue where Thunderbolt Controller shows Yellow Bang (code 43) in Device Manager when the system sleeps overnight with a TBT4 dock with an attached external monitor.
  • Fixed an issue where multiple firmware updates at the same time may fail.
a083ebc5138e5e071ef7270cc9a8280722cc7adf.Name: ThinkPad X1 Carbon 9th / X1 Yoga 6th
a083ebc5138e5e071ef7270cc9a8280722cc7adf.Summary: Lenovo ThinkPad X1 Carbon 9th / X1 Yoga 6th System Firmware

a083ebc5138e5e071ef7270cc9a8280722cc7adf.Description:
Lenovo System Firmware Version 1.52

New functions or enhancements

  • Modified the description about Intel(R) Total Memory Encryption in BIOS Setup.
  • Updated the Diagnostics module to version 04.24.000.
  • No more support for "Override Windows(R) Screen time-out setting” in BIOS Setup to synchronize with the latest Intelligent Security software.
  • Keyboard backlight status is restored after resuming from sleep state.

Problem fixes

  • Fixed an issue where "Power-On Password Control" settings in BIOS Setup did not work correctly.
  • Fixed an issue where an error message may appear after leaving the system over night at Boot Menu with USB-C to Ether adapter.
  • Fixed an issue where touch panel might not work on Linux after resume, if "Linux S3" is set on "Sleep State" in BIOS Setup.
  • Improved the performance in performance mode on Linux.
  • Fixed an issue where USB device through ThinkPad Universal USB-C Smart Dock may not work at pre-boot.
  • Fixed an issue where user can’t go back to menu when “Exit Discarding Changes” is selected in BIOS Setup.
  • Improved the performance of USB Wireless mouse connected to the docking station.

a083ebc5138e5e071ef7270cc9a8280722cc7adf.Summary: Lenovo ThinkPad X1 Carbon 9th / X1 Yoga 6th System Firmware

  • Update includes a security fix.

New functions or enhancements

  • Updated the Diagnostics module to version 04.21.000.
  • Supported 5.15-5.35 GHz band in Indonesia.

Problem fixes

  • Fixed an issue where Power LED on the docking station did not synchronize with Power LED on system with BIOS 1.49.
